Calculate the Gradient

Gradient.Rd

This method computes the gradients of the outputs with respect to the input variables, i.e. for all input variable \(i\) and output class \(j\) $$d f(x)_j / d x_i.$$

Gradient(analyzer, data, times_input = FALSE, ignore_last_act = TRUE)

Arguments

analyzer

An instance of the R6 class Analyzer.
data

Either a matrix or a data frame, where each row must describe an input to the network.
times_input

Multiplies the gradients with the input features. This method is called 'Gradient x Inputs'.
ignore_last_act

Calculate the gradients of the output or the preactivation of the output (default: TRUE).

Value

Returns an array of size (dim_in, dim_out, num_data) which contains the gradients for each input variable to the output predictions for each element in the given data.

Examples

library(neuralnet)
nn <- neuralnet( Species ~ .,
                 iris, linear.output = FALSE,
                 hidden = c(10,8), act.fct = "tanh", rep = 1, threshold = 0.5)
# create an analyzer for this model
analyzer = Analyzer$new(nn)

# calculate gradients for the whole dataset
Gradient(analyzer, data = iris[,-5])
